The paper deals with joint source-channel coding in sensor networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of Gaussian random processes suggests that the paper may also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the optimization aspect of the paper may also make it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
